This paper discusses privacy-enhancing technology and anonymous communication networks, which are relevant to the computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of decentralization, which is relevant to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses possible attacks on the Tor network, which is relevant to the cryptography and security (cs.CY) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the current status of various anonymous networking technologies, which is relevant to the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
